@node "Features" "Features"
                    
                             Features

As you (maybe) know, there are a lot of different computer generators for
various graphic "stuff": scenery generators, fractal generators, cloud
generators... and why not Galaxy generator?

It can draw all kinds of spiral galaxies, no matter how many arms they have,
how big they are, or whatever you can imagine. Manually, you can edit them
in any way, and you could even use it as (manual) cloud generator! Maybe it
isn't so usefull, but is a nice thing, and I hope you like it:)

Complete idea rises when I saw pan-cake intro from %gillette%. I bet that it
could be done in AMOS;) And no, it couldn't... but I've made main routine
for galaxy drawing.

It stands long on my hard, I was afraid of making GUI, and one night, I gave
it to some @{"friends" link "Thanks" 0}. Words of support I've heard, and some time after, whole
project is finished. Rest is history...

Following versions (if any) should be just minor updates... till v2.0 which
should be completely rewritten in C.
@endnode

@node "Install" "Installation"

                                Installation

Instalation is @{b}very@{ub} simple... just copy all files anywhere and that's
that... You may use GalaxyCreator.lib if you have AMOS.library in your libs:
Othervise, you must use GalaxyCreator. Of course, you can delete unusable
version.
@endnode

@node "Gadgets" "Gadgets"

                                   Gadgets

                                       Colours:@{"R" link "RGB" 0} @{"G" link "RGB" 0} @{"B" link "RGB" 0}
                                                  @{"1" link "1234C" 0}
                                          Draw:@{"4" link "1234C" 0} @{"C" link "1234C" 0} @{"2" link "1234C" 0}
                                          @{"Same" link "Same" 0}   @{"3" link "1234C" 0}
                                       Start d.:@{"   " link "Starting d." 0}
                                           Step:@{"   " link "Step" 0}
              @{"Mouse draw" link "Mouse draw" 0}                 Angle:@{"    " link "Angle" 0}
                                          Dense:@{"   " link "Dense" 0}
                                       @{"Redense" link "Redense" 0} @{"Cls" link "Cls" 0}
                                       @{"ģDRAWĢ" link "DRAW" 0}  @{"UnDo" link "Undo" 0}
                                       @{"Save" link "Save" 0}    @{"Load" link "Save" 0}
                                       @{"Save IFF" link "Save IFF" 0}
                                       @{"About" link "About" 0}  @{"Quit" link "Quit" 0}

@{"Screen Cycle" link "Screen cycle" 0}  @{"Default settings" link "Dsettings" 0}
@endnode

@node "RGB" "RGB"
This three gadgets allows you to change the galaxy palette.
@endnode

@node "1234C" "1,2,3,4,C"
Clicking on theese gadgets will define which galaxy arms will be drawn. 'C'
gadget is for galaxy center.
@endnode

@node "Same" "Same"
If this option is turned on, all galaxy arms will be the same. This is
faster, but not so realistic, and should be turned on for experimenting only
and turned off for final picture.
@endnode

@node "Starting d." "   "
This string gadget allows entering of diameter from which the arms of the
galaxy will be drawed.
@endnode

@node "Step" "   "
This string gadget allows you to change the step of a spiral.
@endnode

@node "Angle" "    "
This is gadget where you may enter the galactic arms angle.
@endnode

@node "Dense" "   "
This is dense of the galaxy.
@endnode

@node "Redense" "Redense"
Yes, a funny name it is... If this gadget is turned off, the galaxies will
be "normal". Else, well... @{"try it" link "NGC6946" 0} for yourself.
@endnode

@node "DRAW" "ģDRAWĢ"
This gadget starts drawing of your galaxy. You can stop drawing by pressing
both mouse buttons.
@endnode

@node "UnDo" "UnDo"
You should use this gadget if you want to cancel your previous operation
(such as @{"Draw" link "DRAW" 0}, @{"Cls" link "Cls" 0} or @{"Mouse draw" link "Mouse draw" 0}, but not UnDo:) This option doesn't affect
your data, just picture.
@endnode

@node "Cls" "Cls"
If this gadget is turned on, every click on @{"ģDRAWĢ" link "DRAW" 0} will clear the whole
galaxy screen before drawing anything. Also, doubleclick on this gadget will
clear galaxy screen immediately.
@endnode

@node "Save" "Save & Load"
Load and Save gadgets will load and save galaxy data (in fact, all of your
settings), which can be more than 100 times shorter then @{"ILBM picture" link "Save IFF" 0}!!!

See also @{"Default settings" link "Dsettings" 0}
@endnode

@node "Save IFF" "Save IFF"
This gadget allows you to save whole galaxy as IFF ILBM file.
@endnode

@node "About" "About"
This gadget, if pressed, will eat your dog for breakfast!
@endnode

@node "Quit" "Quit"
Guess what;))
@endnode

@node "Mouse draw" "Mouse draw"
If you move the pointer on this area, you will notice that it's changed into
a crosshair. By pressing left mouse button, you may draw anything you want.
@{"Dense" link "Dense" 0} parameter is valuable here. By pressing right mouse button, you delete
everything under the crosshair.
@endnode

@node "Screen cycle" "Screen Cycle"
Yes, Galaxy Creator don't open a system screen... but you can switch to
system screens at any time by pressing LeftAmiga+A. And returning on the
GalaxyCreator screen works in the same way.
@endnode

@node "Dsettings" "Default settings"
It's very easy to change default settings. Just made them, and save them as
@{fg shine}Default.gcd@{fg text} in GalaxyCreator's default directory.
@endnode

